claim.claim-text:
A linear actuator (100, 200) comprising:
a coil (40) that is movably provided;
a magnetic body (50, 250) that is provided to move integrally with the coil (40);
a first yoke (11, 211) that extends outside of the coil (40);
a second yoke (12, 212) that is surrounded by the coil (40), extends, and is opposed to the first yoke (11, 211); and
a magnet (30) that forms a magnetic field between the first yoke (11, 211) and the second yoke (12, 212),
wherein
the magnetic body (50, 250) that has a first leg portion (51, 261, 271) and a second leg portion (52, 262, 272) extending along an axis of the coil (40), respectively, and has a bottom portion (53, 263, 273) connecting the first leg portion (51, 261, 271) and the second leg portion (52, 262, 272), and the first leg portion (51, 261, 271) extends from the bottom portion (53, 263, 273) through an inside of the coil (40) in an axis direction of the coil (40) and the second leg portion (52, 262, 272) extends in the axis direction of the coil (40) passing from the bottom portion (53, 263, 273) through an outside of the coil (40), and
the first yoke (11, 211) and the second yoke (12, 212) respectively have a first support portion (14, 214) and a second support portion (15, 215), the first support portion (14, 214) and the second support portion (15, 215) supporting each end portion of the first leg portion (51, 261, 271) and the second leg portion (52, 262, 272) of the magnetic body (50, 250) in a stop state, wherein the first support portion (14, 214) and the second support portion (15, 215) have magnetic polarities opposite to each other.
